 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of documents specifying aspects of a product including
     design, process, material, tests and programming languages.
   </p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   <li>specification of technology used for parts and part families;</li>
   <li>specification describing an activity to be performed on a Product or Material;</li>
   <li>specification of properties applicable to surface textures or coatings;</li>
   <li>specification of the characteristics and constraints necessary for correct interoperation between specified units;</li>
   <li>specification defining the syntax and semantics of a computer interpretable language;</li>
   <li>specification of properties applicable to raw material, mixtures, or semi-fabricated material;</li>
   <li>specification of information about the physical or functional testing of a Product;</li>
   <li>structured texts that can have relationships to other structured texts for definition of any of these specifications;</li>
   <li>association between a Specification definition and one or more Products;</li>
